;User Control: Deciding who can collect your data
Ruchajinem rub'i' winäq: Rujikib'axik achike nitikïr nimolo richin ri taq atzij


;We should all be able to choose – with clarity and confidence – what information we share with what companies, understanding the tradeoffs we’re making when we do.
Qonojel k'o chi yojtikïr yojcha'on – rik'in ch'ajch'ojil chuqa' kuqub'äl k'u'x – achike etamab'äl yeqakomonij kik'in ri taq ajk'ayij, akuchi' niq'ax pa qawi' ri taq ch'ojilal tajin niqab'än.


;Right now, we all lack meaningful choice online – privacy policies are often miles long and hard to read, we don’t understand what information we’re sharing or when, and opting out is seldom on the menu.
Wakami qonojel nik'atzin jun utziläj chi ya'öl na'oj chi qe pa k'amab'ey – ri ichinan taq na'ojil junelïk taq nïm raqän taq xo'il k'ayewal richin yesik'ïx, man qetaman ta achike taq etamab'äl tajin yeqakomonij o jampe', chuqa' ri opting out man jutaqil ta k'o pa k'utüy samaj.


;91% of adults agree that consumers have lost control of how personal information is collected and used by companies.
91% chi ke ri nimawinaqi' kiya'on chi kiwäch chi ri loq'onela' kisachon ri jikomal achikem rub'eyal ri ketamab'al nimol chuqa' nokisäx kuma ri taq ajk'ayij.


